radiographic_examinations.findings: The gallbladder is distended with a sludge level noted, interval development of gallbladder wall thickening, and a stone impacted within the neck of the gallbladder. The liver appears normal with note of pneumobilia. A CBD stent is in place. No ascites present. Small lymph nodes noted in the porta hepatis region. A small cyst in the liver adjacent to the gallbladder fossa.
